# Normalize line endings so the repository always stores text files with LF,
# regardless of which OS a contributor commits from. This keeps diffs clean
# (no whole-file "everything changed" noise when an editor flips CR/LF) and
# avoids CRLF breaking shell scripts on the Linux box we deploy to.
#
# `text=auto` lets Git detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` forces LF in the repo.
# Add per-type overrides here if a file genuinely needs CRLF (e.g. Windows
# batch files: `*.bat text eol=crlf`).
* text=auto eol=lf
